  <summary date="2001-08-02" status="Introduced">Medicare Preservation Act of 2001 - Amends the Economic Growth and Tax Relief Reconciliation Act of 2001 to move up from October 1, 2001, to September 24, 2001, the due date of any required installment of corporate estimated tax otherwise due on September 15.Authorizes the Secretary of the Treasury to waive any penalty or addition to tax imposed on the failure to make such required installment if the installment is made on or before October 1, 2001.</summary>
